Python中的encode()和decode()函数：

          encode                   decode
           编码                     解码
Unicode ---------> gbk,utf-8,etc. ---------> Unicode
 (str)                (bytes)                 (str)



str.encode(encoding="utf-8", errors="strict")
    Return an encoded version of the string as a bytes object. Default encoding is 'utf-8'. errors may be given to set a different error handling scheme. The default for errors is 'strict', meaning that encoding errors raise a UnicodeError.

bytes.decode(encoding="utf-8", errors="strict")
bytearray.decode(encoding="utf-8", errors="strict")
    Return a string decoded from the given bytes. Default encoding is 'utf-8'. errors may be given to set a different error handling scheme. The default for errors is 'strict', meaning that encoding errors raise a UnicodeError.